<p>
We are delighted to announce the release of <a href=3D"https://github.com/S=
olo5/solo5/releases/tag/v0.12.0">Solo5 0.12.0</a>. This has two distinct fe=
atures: a new hvt <a href=3D"https://github.com/Solo5/solo5/pull/640">backe=
nd for DragonFlyBSD nvmm</a>, thanks to first-time contributor Michael Neum=
ann, and <a href=3D"https://github.com/Solo5/solo5/pull/647">soft power-off=
 of virtio unikernels</a> - a <a href=3D"https://github.com/Solo5/solo5/iss=
ues/499">long-standing feature request</a>, which makes using solo5 e.g. on=
 Google compute much smoother &ndash; this was initially requested by Micha=
el Bacarella, including draft implementations, and <a href=3D"https://githu=
b.com/Solo5/solo5/pull/647">now implemented</a> and merged by Romain Calasc=
ibetta.
